Bola Ahmed Tinubu, the newly sworn-in President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, has extended an arm of fellowship to his opponents in the February 25 2023 presidential election, saying that he sees them as fellow patriots and that he would continue to treat them so. He also added that their current legal pursuits at the courts challenging his victory at the poll are an exercise of their constitutional rights which he, Tinubu also supports. Details later.